AFTER ECR

Host an instance for eks
allow port 8080
connect it with terminal

connect the IAM user
aws configure

attach role - modify IAM roles attach it with instance

sir's repo eks-cluster-creating

set root password
------
vim /etc/ssh/sshd_config 40,65
restart enable sshd

Go to Jenkins -> system
add ssh server
name- eks-node
root

advance password based

setup ssh between docker and eks-node

ssh-copy-id root@ip-viceversa


THEN TRANSFER FILE from docker regapp-deploy.yaml and regapp-service.yaml to eks node
copy ecr image id and paste in container image of both the files

post build action
add server
Jenkins eks node
/

exec-

kubectl apply -f regapp-deploy.yaml
kubectl apply -f regapp-service.yaml

build now on Jenkins

kubectl get pod
kubectl get svc

copy the svc id and paste with :8080


